<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0082</SECOND>
<HEAD>New Tulsa Correspondent Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TULSA, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Douglas Ferguson, night supervisor in the
Oklahoma City bureau of The Associated Press, has been named AP
correspondent in Tulsa.
   The appointment was announced Thursday by Oklahoma City Chief of
Bureau Lindel Hutson.
   Ferguson, 26, joined the AP in Oklahoma City in 1987.
Previously, he worked at The Norman (Okla.) Transcript.
   He is a native of La Jolla, Calif., and a graduate of Abilene
Christian University in Texas.
</TEXT>
