<FIRST>u i BC-Salvador-Chronology     11-17 0275</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Salvador-Chronology,0282</SECOND>
<HEAD>Salvador Killings in Recent Months</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The following is a partial list
of killings in El Salvador since President Alfredo Cristiani took
office on June 1.
   _ June 9: Antonio Rodriguez Porth, a conservative ideologist and
aide to Cristiani, is slain by unidentified assassins.
   _ June 26: Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front, the
guerrilla group that has been fighting the government for 10 years,
kills Fire Chief Col. Roberto Armando Rivera, accusing him of
belonging to rightist death squads.
   _ June 30: Edgar Chacon, founder of the right-wing Institute of
International Relations, is killed by unidentified assailants.
   _ Oct. 10: Unidentified assailants shoot to death Edelmira
Fuentes and her son Luis as they ride in a family car. Mrs. Fuentes
was the wife of Luis Fuentes, a rightist journalist. The car was
usually driven by their other son, army Lt. Mario Fuentes, and
there is speculation he was the target.
   _ Oct. 17: Isabel Casanova, daughter of Army Col. Oscar
Casanova, is killed. An anonymous caller claims responsibility for
the guerrillas, but the FMLN denies it and says the murder is the
work of rightists who want to destroy peace efforts.
   _ Oct. 31: An explosion rips through the headquarters of the
National Federation of Salvadoran Workers, killing 10 union leaders
and wounding another 29. The FMLN accuses the military of
involvement.
   _ Nov. 16: Six Jesuit priests, their housekeeper and her
daughter are killed and mutilated during the worst fighting in the
civil war. The priests included the rector and vice-rector of the
Central American University, one of the most prestigious
educational institutions in the region.
</TEXT>
