<HEAD>Authorities Make Largest Cocaine Bust in Venezuelan History</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities seized nearly 5,000 pounds
of cocaine and arrested five Venezuelans and Colombians in the
largest cocaine bust in the nation's history, officials said.
   The cocaine, which was confiscated by national guard troops, was
being stored in trucks near Valencia, about 100 miles west of
Caracas, guard spokesman Col. Gerardo Marquez said Thursday.
   Along with the estimated 4,840 pounds of cocaine, the national
guard also confiscated $17,380 from the suspects during Wednesday's
raid.
   The identities of the suspects were not released. Marquez said
authorities believe they are linked to Colombian drug cartel
operations.
   Venezuela and neighboring countries have been increasingly used
as alternative smuggling routes for the Colombian cartels since
Colombian authorities launched a U.S.-backed crackdown in August.
