<HEAD>Rape Defendant Who Punched Attorney in Front of Jury Convicted</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs final grafs 7-8 with 2 grafs to move up first reference
to judge. Isaih is cq in 2nd graf. Note contents of 5th graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who punched his public defender in the
face as a jury looked on has been convicted of the charges that
brought him to court in the first place.
   Isaih Johnson Grady's blow left Assistant Public Defender John
Benito crumpled on the floor Wednesday.
   Bailiffs quickly subdued Grady. Benito was taken to a hospital,
where he received several stitches near his eye.
   Grady, 31, was found guilty Thursday on all seven counts against
him _ rape, robbery, burglary and two counts each of kidnapping and
aggravated assault in a May 19 attack on a woman.
   The punching occurred in the first hour of Grady's trial. Grady
knocked his lawyer to the floor, then stood over him and yelled,
``Don't call me no nigger,'' something witnesses said they never
heard Benito say.
   Grady was chained to his chair Wednesday and Thursday,
delivering his own closing argument that way.
   Circuit Judge Manuel Menendez Jr. ruled that by punching Benito,
Grady had discharged his attorney.
   Throughout his court appearances, Grady called Benito an
incompetent ``donkey'' and also insulted Menendez, who scheduled
sentencing for Jan. 5.
