<FIRST>r i AM-Israel-Unrest     11-17 0362</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Israel-Unrest,0373</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soldiers Wound 15, Arabs Stab Two Palestinians in Occupied Lands</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soldiers shot and wounded 15 Palestinians in
the occupied lands Friday and Palestinian militants stabbed and
injured two fellow Arabs they suspected of collaborating with
Israeli authorities.
   The army prepared to call up two reserve units of Jewish
settlers to serve in the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip, Israel
radio and the independent Maariv newspaper reported.
   Maariv said the units would begin deployment in early December,
with one unit serving in Jericho and the other seeing duty
throughout the West Bank.
   It said a similar unit was called up 10 days ago to patrol
Jericho. If the report is true, it would be the first settler
reserve patrol in the West Bank since the Palestinian uprising
began 23 months ago.
   The scheduled deployment caused a furor among left-wing
legislators, who said units of right-wing settlers could increase
violence in the occupied territories.
   Critics also said deployment of the reserve ``regional defense
units,'' which in the occupied territories are primarily comprised
of setters, could politicize the army.
   In Israel, all Jewish men through age 54 serve up to 40 days
annual reserve duty. Until a spate of settler attacks against Arabs
several years ago, settlers often were assigned to reserve duty by
their homes.
   At least 615 Palestinians have been killed by Israelis in the
uprising and 42 Israelis have died. Twenty-four of the Arab deaths
have been attributed to settlers and the rest were killed by
soldiers.
   In the occupied West Bank, four Palestinians were wounded by
army gunfire and one Arab was shot in a clash with settlers, Arab
reporters said.
   The army confirmed one wounded in the West Bank by army gunfire
and said the military was investigating reports that a Palestinian
in the town of Ramallah was shot and wounded by settlers.
   In the Gaza Strip, 10 Palestinians were wounded in clashes with
troops.
   Two Arabs in Gaza City were stabbed and beaten by Palestinian
activists on suspicion of cooperating with Israeli authorities.
   At least 146 Arabs have been killed by fellow Palestinians
during the uprising on suspicion of collaborating with Israel.
</TEXT>
