<FIRST>r i AM-PuertoRico-Democrats     11-17 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Puerto Rico-Democrats,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Democratic Leader Says Bush Has Not Provided Leadership</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The chairman of the Democratic
National Committee said Friday President Bush has not shown
leadership in the face of such world events as the war in El
Salvador and the changes in Eastern Europe.
   ``We ought to be focusing on what is happening in our own
hemisphere and providing leadership there. That has not been
forthcoming,'' Ron Brown said at the opening of the association of
state Democratic leaders meeting in Puerto Rico.
   ``In Europe and the emerging democracies around this world one
of the biggest disappointments is that where America provided
leadership in the past we are now following, trying to catch up,
and seem surprised by every turn of events,'' he said.
   Brown said Democrats in Congress will try to fill the gap left
by Bush in the international scene, but he did not elaborate.
   The meeting ends Saturday.
</TEXT>
