<HEAD>Coast Guard Recovers 200 Pounds of Cocaine Floating In Ice Chests</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Coast Guard said it recovered
about 200 pounds of cocaine Thursday floating in three ice chests
near the offshore island of Vieques.
   The cocaine was stacked in bricks inside each ice chest, the
Coast Guard said in a statement without indicating the street value
of the drugs.
   It said the recovery was made by the Coast Guard cutter Attu
during a patrol. Officials searched beaches in Vieques for more
cocaine but found none, it said.
   The statement said so far this year the Coast Guard has seized
7,548 pounds of cocaine in waters off Puerto Rico.
