<FIRST>r i AM-Canada-Tornado     11-17 0229</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Canada-Tornado,0237</SECOND>
<HEAD>One Killed After Tornado Touches Down in Quebec</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. HILAIRE, Quebec (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The violent series of tornadoes that
hit the eastern United States Thursday crashed into Quebec just
after noon, leaving one person dead, police said.
   The tornado first touched down in the town of Richmond, just
east of St. Hilaire, police said. A man was killed when his car was
hit by a school bus during the high winds in Richmond, Quebec
provincial police official Bertrand Fortin said.
   The victim's name has not been released, said Fortin. None of
the children in the bus were injured.
   Winds of more than 124 mph blew the roof off a shopping mall in
the center of St. Hilaire. The back wall of an office building
behind the mall was demolished before the tornado moved down the
main street, shattering windows and knocking down trees.
   Roofs were torn off buildings, cars were overturned and
mailboxes were thrown hundreds of yards, said a town official in
the small community southeast of Montreal.
   ``The tornado went through like a flash _ maybe 30 seconds _ but
the winds kept up for over an hour,'' said Jeanine Lapalme,
secretary to the mayor.
   There were no deaths reported in St. Hilaire, but a small number
of people were injured in the storm and were taken to hospital in
neighboring communities, said Lapalme.
</TEXT>
