<FIRST>r f PM-Carlton-Paramount     11-17 0215</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Carlton-Paramount,0223</SECOND>
<HEAD>Britain's Carlton In Joint Venture With Paramount</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Carlton Communications PLC, a major British TV and
communications concern, said it has entered into a joint TV
production venture with the U.S. entertainment giant Paramount
Communications Inc.
   Paramount's British unit, Paramount Television Ltd., will buy 49
percent of Carlton's Zenith television production subsidiary for an
undisclosed sum, the companies said in a joint statement Thursday.
   Analysts said the deal enables Zenith to expand faster in the
United States, and gives Paramount a stronger footing in Europe,
whose television networks are being deregulated rapidly.
   The companies said the deal showed Paramount's commitment to
Zenith's development of television programs for the global market.
Paramount will distribute Zenith programs internationally.
   ``This partnership between Carlton and Paramount will add
further strength to Zenith's next stage of development in a rapidly
changing production environment,'' said Bob Phillis, Carlton's
group managing director and chairman of Zenith.
   Mel Harris, president of Paramount's international television
division, said the agreement ``indicates Paramount's long-term
commitment to both global production and to increasing our
partnership activities within the European Community.''
   Zenith, while a small part of Carlton's overall operations, is
Britain's biggest independent television program maker. It supplies
programs to British networks as well as European and U.S. network
and cable companies.
</TEXT>
