<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills fell
in Thursday's action to the lowest level in 17 months.
   The Treasury Department sold $9.8 billion of the bills at an
average discount rate of 7.17 percent, down from 7.35 percent at
the last auction on Oct. 19.
