<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-TCI     11-17 0186</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-TCI,0194</SECOND>
<HEAD>TCI Reports Third-Quarter Loss</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Telecommunications Inc., the nation's largest
cable TV system operator, on Thursday reported a third-quarter loss
of $73.9 million, citing increased interest expenses and losses of
affiliates.
   For the quarter ended Sept. 30, TCI's net loss equaled 21 cents
per share on revenue of $826.5 million. That compared with earnings
of $63.7 million, or 17 cents per share, on revenue of $624 million
for the same period in 1988.
   Losses for the nine-month period that ended Sept. 30 totaled
$188.9 million, or 54 cents per share, compared with a profit of
$34.5 million, or 10 cents per share, for the same period last year.
   Revenue for the nine months was $2.2 billion, compared with $1.7
million in 1988.
   The Denver-based company said the losses were due primarily
lower sales gains, increased interest expenses and increased losses
of affiliates.
   Operating income before depreciation and amortization totaled
$312.2 million for the third quarter and $830.4 million for the
first nine months, compared with $244.2 million in the third
quarter and $666.7 million in the first nine months of 1988.
</TEXT>
