<FIRST>r f BC-DataGeneral-Castro     11-17 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Data General-Castro,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Data General Co-Founder Named Chairman, Leaves President's Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESTBORO, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Edson D. de Castro, co-founder in 1968 of
the Data General Corp., has been named chairman of the computer
maker and will relinquish his roles as president and chief
executive officer.
   Castro, 51, was elevated as the firm's first chairman Wednesday.
   ``I have no plans to retire soon,'' de Castro said.
   He said that as chairman, he will focus on long-term strategy,
which he said had been neglected as Data General stuggled with
slumping minicomputer sales and larger rivals such as Digital
Equipment Corp. and International Business Machines Corp.
   Succeeding de Castro is Ronald L. Skates, 48, Data General's
executive vice president and chief operating officer. Skates is a
former partner at Price Waterhouse, Data General's auditor.
   Herbert J. Richman, another Data General co-founder, was named
vice chairman. Richman, 54, will continue to direct the company's
sales organization.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
